    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-07-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-07-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="139"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d139">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 437.00/11.</note>
                <head>[Extract.]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-07-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 1, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 965.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my dispatch No. 931, of the 16th
                    ultimo, and to my telegram of the same date, I have the honor to report that * *
                    * the Governments of France, Germany, and Great Britain have now formally
                    proposed that this question be submitted to arbitration, and have requested the
                    Cuban Government to suggest a tribunal or person before whom the case can be
                    heard.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John B. Jackson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
